{"serial": "07015", "department_serial": 5, "code": "CC0415", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Sociology of Gender", "ch": "性別社會學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chiang, Chen-Yin"], "ch": ["姜貞吟"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "106"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "總教學中心", "en": "Teaching Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 36, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "性別社會學課程著重於講授與介紹性別議題之發展，探討課題包含性別之社會型構與差異、性別氣質、勞動與就業、政治參與、親密關係、性別與身體、數位性別等領域，進行相關理論講授，並進一步帶領學生討論日常生活的性別相關事件與議題最新的發展趨勢。西蒙波娃名言：On ne naît pas femme, on le devient，我們非天生為女人，而是被逐漸塑造而成女人。男性亦同。每個社會都以不同方式來對待性別，並有不同的規範與行為模式。性別社會學主要在探究社會形構的性別所呈現的社會性別差異，如何受到文化與社會結構的形塑，如何對個體產生影響，以及我們可以如何讓性別結構有不同的實踐。本課程將採互動對話方式，對目前社會性別議題與性別相關政策，進行討論與分析，了解最新的性別政策發展方向。最終，本課程將以情境式設計，讓同學理解特定的、多元的性別處境脈絡，提升性別敏感度，了解性別與不同的社會結構交織後的狀態，以及對性別相關政策的掌握。", "en": "The sociology of gender course focuses on teaching and introducing the development of gender issues, covering topics such as the social construction and differences of gender, gender temperament, labor and employment, political participation, intimate relationships, gender and the body, and digital gender. The course includes lectures on relevant theories and further leads students to discuss the latest development trends in gender-related events and issues in daily life. Simone de Beauvoir‘s famous quote, “One is not born, but rather becomes, a woman,“ underscores that we are not born women but are gradually shaped into women, and the same applies to men. Every society treats gender differently and has different norms and behavior patterns. The main goal of sociology of gender is to explore the social gender differences presented by societal constructions, how they are shaped by culture and social structures, how they affect individuals, and how we can practice different gender structures. This course will adopt an interactive dialogue approach to discuss and analyze current social gender issues and gender-related policies, understanding the latest developments in gender policy. Ultimately, the course will use a situational design to help students understand specific, diverse gender contexts, enhance gender sensitivity, comprehend the state of gender intertwined with different social structures, and grasp gender-related policies."}, "outline": {"ch": "W01：說明課程、性別化的民俗與文化1\nW02：性別化的民俗與文化2\nW03：性別與繼承\nW04：性別與勞動1：家務勞動\nW05：國慶日停課一週\nW06：性別與勞動2：就業勞動\nW07：性別與身體-生殖科技與健康\nW08：期中考\nW09：做男人：現代男子氣慨的展演\nW10：LGBTQIA/跨越性別：模糊性別的界線\nW11：性騷擾與數位性別暴力\nW12：從違反意願到積極同意\nW13：親密關係1：現代親密關係的轉變\nW14：親密關係2：分手安全及分手暴力\nW15：性工作治理及其排除政治\nW16：期末個人作業繳交\nW17：自主學習\nW18：自主學習", "en": "W01: Course Introduction, Gendered Folklore and Culture 1\nW02: Gendered Folklore and Culture 2\nW03: Gender and Inheritance\nW04: Gender and Labor 1: Domestic Labor\nW05: No Classes for National Holiday Week\nW06: Gender and Labor 2: Employment Labor\nW07: Gender and the Body - Reproductive Technologies and Health\nW08: Midterm Exam\nW09: Being a Man: The Display of Modern Masculinity\nW10: LGBTQIA/Gender Crossing: Blurring the Lines of Gender\nW11: Sexual Harassment and Digital Gender Violence\nW12: From Violation to Enthusiastic Consent\nW13: Intimate Relationships 1: The Transformation of Modern Intimate Relationships\nW14: Intimate Relationships 2: Safe Breakups and Breakup Violence\nW15: Governance of Sex Work and Its Politics of Exclusion\nW16: Final Individual Assignment Submission\nW17: Self-directed Learning\nW18: Self-directed Learning"}, "textbook": {"ch": "1. 陳瑤華主編（2014）《台灣婦女處境白皮書：2014年》。台北：女書。\n2. 黃淑玲、游美惠主編（2018）《性別向度與台灣社會》。台北：巨流。（第3版）", "en": "1. Chen Yao-Hua, editor (2014). “White Paper on the Situation of Women in Taiwan: 2014.“ Taipei: Fembooks.\n2. Huang Shu-Ling and You Mei-Hui, editors (2018). “Gender Dimensions and Taiwanese Society.“ Taipei: Chuliu Publishers. (3rd Edition)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "30%", "en": "30%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n\n\n個別指導", "en": ["Lecture", "", "", "Individual Instruction"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "課堂出席20％、課程參與表現20％、期中考30％、期末個人作業30％", "en": "class attendance 20％, course participation performance 20％, midterm exam 30％, final individual assignment 30％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期二10-12點", "en": "Tuesday 10-12 AM"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "自主學習，約時間討論", "en": "Self-directed learning, schedule time for discussion"}, "domain": {"ch": "社會思潮與現象領域", "en": "社會思潮與現象領域"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "邏輯與創新", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "多元與溝通", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "美感與鑑賞", "rating": "(1)非常低", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "關懷與實踐", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(1)VeryLow", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["學制:限學士班。"], "en": ["Type:Undergraduate Program only."]}, "preselecStu": 22, "stuGender": {"male": 21, "Female": 15}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "master": {}, "bachelor": {"4": 5, "3": 6, "2": 19, "1": 6}}, "stus": [{"serial": "1", "stunum": "10*******", "department": "資訊工程學系", "grade": "4", "class": "1", "priority": "1", "isRequired": false, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "2", "stunum": "10*******", "department": "中國文學系", "grade": "4", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRe